Corticosteroids are lifesaving medicines recommend for patients with severe or critical COVID-19*. They should be given along with current standard of care for COVID-19 which includes oxygen and other medications .  They should not be given to patients with non-severe* COVID-19, and when given in such cases it could be harmful to patientsâ€™ health.*A patient has severe COVID-19 when they have signs of pneumonia, severe respiratory distress, and their blood oxygen level is low. A patient has critical COVID-19 when they need life sustaining treatment, have acute respiratory distress syndrome, or have septic shock (evidence of injury to other organs). More.
